    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-03T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-03T21:00:00-05:00" n="414"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.01/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-03T19:00:00-07:00"
                            >January 3, 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Your No. 2.<note n="8" xml:id="d414fn8">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> There is so far as I am aware no objection to Andrade’s government from
                    any quarter and it is meeting with the general <pb facs="0518" n="398"
                        xml:id="pg_398"/> support of the authorities and people. Conditions are
                    practically normal and no counterrevolution is to be feared.</p>
                <p>The Cabinet changes mentioned in my 3, January 2, 5 p.m. would, I find, cause
                    difficulties for internal political reasons and I am glad the Department does
                    not insist on them.</p>
                <p>The decree calling the elections for February 6, 7 and 8 will be issued tomorrow
                    or Monday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
